      "content": "The UN has been a mixed bag of success and failure in the 21st century. While it has played a crucial role in peacekeeping and humanitarian efforts, its inability to prevent major conflicts like those in Syria, Yemen, and Libya highlights significant shortcomings. Its bureaucratic inefficiencies, lack of enforcement power, and the veto power of the five permanent Security Council members often hinder decisive action. In essence, the UN is a necessary but imperfect institution that needs substantial reforms to truly succeed in preventing major conflicts.",
