      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a fair point about the veto power, but when people argue that the whole system is basically broken or even obsolete because it can't stop these wars, do historians treat those views as serious academic critiques, or is it usually seen as more of an extremist/fringe take? like, is there a real consensus on whether the UN is still legitimate?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
